 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To Mrs. Jacob, On her Seat called, The Rocks, in Gloucestershire.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">easy Distance from the Town,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">An hospitable Seat</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">From Crowd and Noise there stands retir'd,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">A sweet and cool Retreat;</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Securely seated on a Rock,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Whence silver Streams descend,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">From Cliffs the Ruins of old Time,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And murmur as they bend.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The antient Honours of the Wood</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Adorn and guard the Pile;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">At humble Distance down it sees</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The fruitful Vallies smile.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Here Woods and Shades, and Grots and Glades,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Feel sultry Summer mild;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Diversify'd a thousand Ways,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And beautifully wild.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When we, amidst the Shades below,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">From the steep Hill descend,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where crystal Streams in Mazes flow,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That tow'ring Elms defend;</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Like  Regions wrapt in Gloom</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">We think the darksome Way,</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That ends in the  Plains,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Fair, flow'ry, calm, and gay.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Romantic Views these Prospects yield,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That feed poetic Fire;</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Each broken Rock, and Cave, and Field,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Hill, and Vale, inspire.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">These various, gay, delightful Scenes,</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Like Paradise appear;</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Serene as ev'ning Sky my Soul,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And hush'd is ev'ry Care.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="9" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A thousand Birds soft warbling join</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The Music of the Trees;</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whose waving Boughs and whisp'ring Leaves,</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Play wanton in the Breeze.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="10" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The happy Genius of the Place,</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Inspire with softest Joys;</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And Contemplation pure as Light,</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">My rap'tur'd Soul employs.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="11" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="41" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Within the Gates new Scenes arise,</l>
     <l n="42" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Which equal Joys disclose;</l>
     <l n="43" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There Beauty, Goodness, Friendship smiles,</l>
     <l n="44" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And gen'rous Plenty flows.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
